## Tech Stack (react-capacitor)

- React 18 + TypeScript + Vite
- Tailwind CSS + shadcn/ui components
- React Router v6
- TanStack Query for async state
- Zustand for client state
- Dexie (IndexedDB) for local-first storage
- Capacitor for native Android/iOS packaging
- Google Drive API for cloud sync (encrypted)
- Web Crypto API (AES-GCM 256-bit, PBKDF2) for data encryption
- Vitest + React Testing Library for tests
- Bun as package manager

## Architecture

```
src/
├── pages/           # Route components (screens)
├── components/      # Reusable UI components (shadcn/ui)
├── hooks/           # Custom React hooks
├── store/           # Zustand state stores
├── lib/
│   ├── db/          # Dexie database schema, migrations, queries
│   ├── sync/        # Google Drive sync logic
│   ├── crypto/      # Web Crypto encryption/decryption utils
│   └── utils/       # General utilities, formatters
├── api/             # External API client (if any)
├── test/            # Test setup, utilities, mocks
│   ├── setup.ts     # jest-dom matchers, fake-indexeddb
│   └── utils.tsx    # renderWithRouter, mock factories
├── App.tsx          # Root component with routing
└── main.tsx         # Entry point
```

## Agent Roster

| Agent | Model | Scope | When used |
|---|---|---|---|
| **app-dev** | Sonnet | `src/` — all app code | RED/GREEN phases |
| **reviewer** | Opus | Full repo (read-only + tests) | PHASE 5 validation |

## Additional Conventions

### Capacitor
- Native plugins: `@capacitor/filesystem`, `@capacitor/share`, `@capacitor/app`
- Platform detection: `import { Capacitor } from '@capacitor/core'`
- Never use browser-only APIs without checking `Capacitor.isNativePlatform()`
- Android builds: `npx cap sync android && npx cap open android`

### Local-First with Dexie
- Dexie is primary storage (offline-first)
- All data available offline; sync is optional enhancement
- Schema versioning via `db.version(N).stores({...})`
- Use `useLiveQuery` for reactive Dexie queries in components

### Encryption
- Web Crypto API for all encryption (AES-GCM 256-bit)
- PBKDF2 for key derivation from user passphrase
- Keys stored in IndexedDB (not localStorage)
- Encrypted before sync to Google Drive

### Testing
- Vitest + React Testing Library + user-event
- Globals enabled (no need to import describe/it/expect/vi)
- `fake-indexeddb` for Dexie tests (imported in test setup)
- Mock Capacitor plugins in tests: `vi.mock('@capacitor/...')`
- Test utilities at `src/test/utils.tsx`
